        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 31 at 4:56PM EDT until July 31 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC</headline>
        <description>SVRLWX

The National Weather Service in Sterling Virginia has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Loudoun County in northern Virginia...
Southeastern Clarke County in northwestern Virginia...
North central Fauquier County in northern Virginia...

* Until 530 PM EDT.

* At 456 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Bluemont, or
14 miles southeast of Millwood Pike, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damaging winds will cause some trees and large branches
to fall. This could injure those outdoors, as well as
damage homes and vehicles. Roadways may become blocked by
downed trees. Localized power outages are possible.
Unsecured light objects may become projectiles.

* Locations impacted include...
Middleburg, Bluemont, Saint Louis, Halfway, Upperville, Philomont,
and Paris.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
